    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="570"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/8–1854</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Prime
                        Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d570fn1">Transmitted to London in telegram 984, Aug. 18,
                        with instructions to the Ambassador to deliver to the Prime Minister.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-18">August 18,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1"
                            >Winston</persName>
                    </hi>: I returned yesterday from a weekend vacation and found your kind
                        message.<note n="2" xml:id="d570fn2">Presumably the message of Aug. 14, <ref
                            target="#pg_1037">p. 1037</ref>.</note> I am honored and heartened that
                    you occasionally follow the low-level of the Foreign Office and not merely the
                    summits.</p>
                <p>I am glad that we are following a common line as regards <persName
                        corresp="#p_MENDESFRANCEP1">Mendes-France</persName>. I agree with you that
                    it is time to bring this chapter to an end. I hope that it will be an <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> ending. I am not clear in my mind as to any
                    alternative which will be both practical and not subject to another succession
                    of parliamentary wrangles.</p>
                <p>Our papers fully report the <persName corresp="#p_ATTLEECB1"
                        >Attlee</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_BEVANA1">Bevan</persName> excursion
                    with many pictures. From our standpoint they do not make a helpful exhibit. I
                    fear we can only exchange condolences on the subject of your last sentence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
